Takes the wrapped value, leaving `Default::default()` in its place.

# Panics

Panics if the value is currently borrowed.

# Examples

```
use std::cell::RefCell;

let c = RefCell::new(5);
let five = c.take();

assert_eq!(five, 5);
assert_eq!(c.into_inner(), 0);
```
